    • Enum Constant Detail

      • NOT_SPECIFIED

        public static final EscapeType NOT_SPECIFIED
        The escape type assigned to template variables that don't specify an inline escape type. For example, the escape type of ~%html:person.address.street% is ESCAPE_HTML whereas the escape type of ~%person.address.street% is NOT_SPECIFIED. It is not allowed to pass this EscapeTye any of the methods in the Renderer class. However, if a template variable's escape type is NOT_SPECIFIED, its value will be escaped using whatever EscapeTye is passed to these methods.

      • ESCAPE_NONE

        public static final EscapeType ESCAPE_NONE
        Do not apply any escaping. This is (most likely) the EscapeType to use if a template variable stands in for an entire block of HTML. Anything that was variable in there has has likely already been substituted and escaped somewhere upstream. Further escaping would destroy the HTML tags themselves. This escape type can be specified within the template variable itself using the text prefix. For example: ~%text:tableRows%

      • ESCAPE_HTML

        public static final EscapeType ESCAPE_HTML
        The type of escaping to be used for template variables inserted into HTML tags. For example: 

         <tr><td>~%fullName%</td></tr>

        This escape type can be specified within the template variable itself using the html prefix: 

         <tr><td>~%html:fullName%</td></tr>

      • ESCAPE_JS

        public static final EscapeType ESCAPE_JS
        The type of escaping to be used for template variables inserted into Javascript. For example: 

         <script>
  var fullName = "~%fullName%";
 </script>

        This escape type can be specified within the template variable itself using the js prefix: 

         <script>
  var fullName = '~%js:fullName%';
 </script>

      • parse

        public static EscapeType parse​(String s)
        Parses the specified string into an EscapeType. Valid values are "text", "html" and "js", corresponding to the available variable type prefixes (e.g. ~%html:fullName%). The string is also allowed to be null or empty, in which case this method returns null. This corresponds to a variable without a type prefix (~%fullName%).
        Parameters:
        s - The string to parse
        Returns:
        The EscapeType corresponding to the string
